title: Bethlehem Catholic girls volleyball team tops Freedom (PHOTOS)
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Bethlehem Catholic’s girls volleyball team breezed by a crosstown rival on Wednesday night, sweeping Freedom 25-21, 25-13, 25-9, in an Eastern Pennsylvania Conference Steel Division contest. 
Rachel Tanczos had 13 kills and Jordan Young registered 11 kills for the Golden Hawks. Rachel Cray dished out 24 assists. 
Hailey Silfies paced the Patriots with five kills and three blocks. 
Scroll through the gallery atop the post to see images from Wednesday.
